    <div class="tab-pane active" id="tab1">
      Unlike to the GitLab-CI, Polytene doesn't require the same authentication data (login, password) used in GitLab. To use all Polytene functionality you must fill all your profile fields instead:
      <ul>
        <li><b>Gitlab url</b> - Polytene need to know about Gitlab instance. Will clone repos from there.</li>
        <li><b>Gitlab ci url</b> - Polytene need to know about GitlabCI instance. Will import projects from there.</li>
        <li><b>Gitlab private token</b> - Polytene need to know about this token because of repo cloning privileges.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="tab-pane" id="tab2">
      All Builds in Polytene are created by the action of GitLab-CI webhooks. So remember to update webhook url, in GitLab-CI after project import. Webhook url can be obtained in Polytene Project details page.
    </div>

    <div class="tab-pane" id="tab3">
      All deployment variables can be defined in branch context of specified Project. Due to this, remeber that every build must have corresponding Project Branch created.
    </div>

